<div class="flex flex-col gap-5">
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="background-color:#13233A;color:#ececec;">
            Help
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div>
                This is a quick tutorial on how to use the Packages feature, which is designed to log Guest Packages.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="background-color:#13233A;color:#ececec;">
            New Guest Package
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div>
                New Guest Package is a form containing 4 fields (Boxes) in which you can fill out. Once filled out, hit the Submit Package to create a new Guest Package.
            </div>
            <div>
                If you receive multiple packages under the same name, it's best if you log each one separately.
            </div>
            <div>
                <table class="mt-5">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Field</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Guest Name</td>
                        <td>This is the name on the package</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Package Description</td>
                        <td>What does the package look like? what's the size?</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Location Stored</td>
                        <td>The location of the package</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Notes</td>
                        <td>
                            Useful to add notes. For example, if a guest called ahead of time to notify us, we can put that in the notes.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="background-color:#13233A;color:#ececec;">
            Received Tab
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            When clicking the <button type="button" class="luxury-light square btn-link">Received</button> button, you'll see a list of jobs that have been logged and stored.

            <div class="mt-2">
                <div>
                    If a guest has picked up their package or you need to update the notes click the
                    <button type="button" class="btn-link btn-icon">
                        <i class="ph ph-pencil-simple-line" style="color:#1a3f5f;"></i>
                    </button>
                    and a pop up will appear with a checkbox and note field.
                    <p>Ticking "Mark as Picked Up" with move the package from the Received Tab to the Picked Up Tab.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <span class="text-bold">To view the package's notes</span> click the
                    <button type="button" class="btn-link btn-icon">
                        <i class="ph ph-notebook" style="color:#1a3f5f;"></i>
                    </button>
                    and a pop up will appear with the package's notes.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="background-color:#13233A;color:#ececec;">
            Completed Tab
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            Similar to the Received Tab, The Picked Up Tab shows Packages that have been collected.
        </div>
    </div>
</div>